<span class="postbody">Well Minymezz, I am happy for you if you get groups left and right and don´t even have to put LFG up. But that is not what happens in most servers. My server is low populated at this time (Morell-Thule), and LFG downtime is an issue for everyone.
<br />

<br />
Though, I do agree that shortening KEI will not solve anything. Most people whines are related to the fact that chanters nowadays have no role whatsoever to do. Having a chanter in group brings no utility to group these days. That´s the core of the problem, DoN solves nothing in that respect.
<br />

<br />
When a zone is new there is lots of mezzing to do, but after people learnt the pathing and the mob frenzy radious is back to single pulling. In any case, don´t fool yourself, if you are getting DoN invites is due to the fact of people noobness to DoN adventures, and mostly due to not finding a FDzer or a bard LFG (or because they are friends and put up with having a chanter in group).
<br />

<br />
Slowing, nuking like a 49 wiz and rare mezzing wasn´t on my contract when I started a chanter. If you find that rewarding enough to keep playing your chanter, then the more power to you. But that does not give you the right to tell everyone else to shut up and suck it up, since you are not the one paying the bills. 
<br />

<br />
Most chanters left the game because of not bringing any utility to groups and slow/nuke boredom. 
<br />

<br />
Myself, I made a bard which while not being my main is what I play (Bard has 500+ AAs, is PoTime, KT and Qvic flagged and has better gear than chanter. My chanter will always be my main at heart though, but unfortunately there is nothing SoE has to offer that makes me want to play her again). I do resent the fact of having to throw my chanter out of the window after getting PoTime and KT flagged, with 600+ AAs... and will shortly move to WoW.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Oh, and gratz on your guild getting you epic 1.5 and GL getting Time flagged. You only gotta loot 1 drop at PH3 these days for it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
